# Fibonacci Heap

The following program implements a Fibonacci Heap for analyzing its algorithmic complexity.

- Homework 1 Specification - https://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~ds1/hw/2-fibheap/problem.html
- Basic Rules - https://kam.mff.cuni.cz/~ds1/hw/rules.html

## Project Structure

- heapgen.cpp   - Generates input to fibheap.c
- fibheap.c     - Main starting point that reads input from stdin
- heap.c/h      - Defines all top-level heap operations (reset, insert, extract_min, decrease_key)
- node.c/h      - Defines low-level node operations on heap nodes (init, free, merge, join, find_min)
- operation.c/h - Converts strings from heapgen into structures

## Building and Running

### Prerequisites:
- gcc/g++
- make

### To Build:

$ make

Run all tests with:

$ bash ./fibheaptest.sh

### To Clean:

$ make clean

